1. Dialogue Platform established, Declaration on Dialogue signed by the presidency of Bosnia and Herzegovina;
2. More than 20% of the population has been reached through various project activities, apprx. 29% of BiH population  participated through communications and Grants Facility activities;
3. Preliminary indicators show that this target is achieved - still awaiting survey for final data;
4. Target partially met as two Dialogue Platform Conferences were organized. Third Dialogue Platform Conference planned for 2016. Youth Forums mechanism established as a channel for communication between youth and decision makers;
5. Three initiatives instigated in 2015 as a result of Youth Forums: 1. Youth civic engagement initiative, 2.  Collaboration of youth and academia as support to local government for more efficient service providing, 3. collaboration of students of Political Sciences form Banja Luka, Sarajevo and Mostar on joint academic research ad exchange;
6. The results for this target are pending and will be known in 2016 upon completion of the KAP survey;

1. Tourism potentials of Via Dinarica in BiH have been promoted through numerous presentations and meetings, published articles and blogs, website, different events, social media pages;
2. Support to small business/tourism organizations and BBs has been provided through implementation of small grant schemes, where 6 tourism service providers and 4 BBs were awarded grants for improvement of their service provision thus increasing their productive economics;
3. 254km of White Trail GPS marked and assessed, while approx. 306 km of GPS tracks for mountain biking included in the database. 233 km of Green Trail GPS marked and assessed, while 425 km of GPS tracks (arteries and variants) included in the database;
4. 37 organizations underwent capacity building and best-practices sharing workshops on the subject of Coaching and capacity development for eco-tour operators and tourism service providers;
5. Via Dinarica has been further promoted through publishing of 10 blogs, 8 double-page articles in daily newspapers, 4 newspaper and TV interviews, while the total outreach through social media was 399,565 views;
6. Through small grant schemes and capacity building workshops, relevant stakeholders were assisted in the design of tourism packages.

